    Overview

    Meet the MarshMellow Comforter: soft, plush, and impossibly cozy.
    It’s double-stuffed for that ultra-fluffy, marshmallow feel that hugs you just right.


    Made with A-Class baby-grade fabric and heat-adaptive vegan fill, it keeps you warm when it’s cold and cool when it’s not perfectly balanced for every season.

    • Double-Stuffed - Literally 2X the filling

    • Temperature-Balancing Fibers – cozy, never hot

    • OEKO-TEX® Class I Certified – baby-safe, hypoallergenic, and chemical-free

    • 100% Vegan – cruelty-free down alternative

    • Fully Machine Washable – no cover or dry cleaning needed


    Materials

    Class 1 Baby-Grade Fabric
    Silky-smooth and breathable. Certified safe for even the most sensitive skin.


    Double-Stuffed Down Alternative Fill
    Plush microfiber fill engineered to mimic real down but cleaner, lighter, and cruelty-free.
    The double-stuffed design keeps it evenly fluffy with no clumping, even after washing.


    OEKO-TEX® Certified: Hypoallergenic, safe for sensitive skin, and responsibly made with ethical and eco-friendly processes.

    Naia™ Sustainable Filling: Silky-smooth, breathable, and biodegradable, made from sustainably sourced materials for comfort you can feel good about.

    FAQ

    What makes the MarshMellow Comforter different from other comforters?

    Most comforters flatten or clump over time. The MarshMellow Comforter is double-stuffed with advanced, heat-adaptive vegan fibers and wrapped in A-Class baby-grade fabric. It’s engineered to stay ultra-fluffy, soft, and perfectly balanced year-round giving you that “sleeping in a marshmallow” feeling every night.


    Will it keep me too hot while I sleep?

    No, that’s the beauty of it. The MarshMellow Comforter uses temperature-balancing fibers that adapt to your body heat. You’ll stay cozy when it’s cool and comfortable when it’s warm, so you never wake up sweaty or chilled.


    Is the MarshMellow Comforter safe for sensitive skin?

    Absolutely. The shell fabric is OEKO-TEX® STANDARD 100 Class I certified, meaning it meets the highest global safety standards and is even safe for babies. It’s hypoallergenic, antibacterial, and completely free of harsh chemicals or irritants.


    Do I need a duvet cover?

    You can use one if you prefer, but it’s not necessary. The MarshMellow Comforter is made from buttery-soft, cloud-like fabric that feels luxurious on its own. Plus, it’s fully machine washable, so it’s effortless to care for.


    Will the filling shift or clump over time?

    Not at all. Our precision box-stitch construction locks the filling in place to prevent any bunching or shifting, even after repeated washing. It stays fluffy, even, and cloud-like for years.

    Is it machine washable?

    Yes! You can toss the entire comforter in your washing machine, no dry cleaning or covers to remove. Wash cold on a gentle cycle with mild detergent, and hang to dry. Washing Instructions

    What’s inside the comforter?

    Each MarshMellow Comforter is filled with a premium, cruelty-free microfiber blend that mimics the plush loft of down but without the allergens, animal materials, or odor. It’s 100% vegan, clean, and sustainably sourced.


    How thick or heavy is it?

    It’s double-stuffed for maximum fluff and comfort, yet still lightweight and breathable. Most customers describe it as “the perfect balance,” plush enough for a cozy winter night, breathable enough for year-round use.


    Can I use it all year round?

    Yes! The MarshMellow Comforter is designed as an all-season comforter. Its adaptive fill regulates temperature naturally, making it ideal for every month of the year.


    What sizes does it come in?

    It’s available in Twin, Full/Queen, and King/California King, designed with a generous drape for that luxurious, hotel-style look and feel.
